		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Gleiwitz incident</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Sender_gliwice.jpg" class="image" title="Gliwice Radio Tower today. It is the highest wooden structure in Europe."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0c/Sender_gliwice.jpg/250px-Sender_gliwice.jpg" width="250" height="333" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Sender_gliwice.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="/wiki/Gliwice_Radio_Tower" title="Gliwice Radio Tower">Gliwice Radio Tower</a> today. It is the highest wooden structure in Europe.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Gleiwitz incident</b>, sometimes incorrectly referred to as <b>Operation Canned Goods</b>, was <a href="/wiki/False_flag" title="False flag">a staged attack</a> on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1939-08-31"><a href="/wiki/August_31" title="August 31">31 August</a> <a href="/wiki/1939" title="1939">1939</a></span> against the <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> <a href="/wiki/Radio_station" title="Radio station" class="mw-redirect">radio station</a> <i>Sender Gleiwitz</i> in <a href="/wiki/Gleiwitz" title="Gleiwitz" class="mw-redirect">Gleiwitz</a>, <a href="/wiki/Upper_Silesia" title="Upper Silesia">Upper Silesia</a>, <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a> (since 1945: <a href="/wiki/Gliwice" title="Gliwice">Gliwice</a>, <a href="/wiki/Poland" title="Poland">Poland</a>) on the eve of <a href="/wiki/European_Theatre_of_World_War_II" title="European Theatre of World War II">World War II in Europe</a>.</p>
<p>This provocation was the best known of several actions in <a href="/wiki/Operation_Himmler" title="Operation Himmler">Operation Himmler</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Nazi_Germany" title="Nazi Germany">Nazi Germany</a> <a href="/wiki/Schutzstaffel" title="Schutzstaffel">SS</a> project to create the appearance of Polish aggression against Germany, which would be used to justify the subsequent <a href="/wiki/Invasion_of_Poland_(1939)" title="Invasion of Poland (1939)">invasion of Poland</a>.</p>
